g.title: j862181451
g.text: Check boolean EleanorIndifference

g.title: j1758492563
g.text: Are you there? I need to talk.

g.title: j862181451->j1758492563
g.text: true

g.title: j1254392454
g.text: Are you there? I need to talk to you about something. It’s serious.

g.title: j862181451->j1254392454
g.text: false

g.title: j2430953547
g.text: Right here.

g.title: j25010297
g.text: Really sorry. Not right now. [End.]

g.title: j402916129
g.text: I’m here. Go ahead.

g.title: j3741280134
g.text: Remember how I told you about how I tried to touch Rusalka’s mind with mine, and I made contact with The Indifference instead?

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j4155696737
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j2350018177
g.text: Of course I remember.

g.title: j16567716
g.text: Do you understand what happened to Major Rusalka?

g.title: j2941716710
g.text: Right. I wasn’t ready to talk about it then. I’m ready now, if you’re willing.

g.title: j668779149
g.text: She was being used. The Indifference was puppeting her.

g.title: j1234520935
g.text: Pretty sure she was hollowed out and driven around like a... well... Warframe...?

g.title: j3611008168
g.text: If you’re sure.

g.title: j2855000709
g.text: ‘The Indifference’. That’s what you call it?

g.title: j763409226
g.text: Hollowed out, yes.

g.title: j3325775330
g.text: I’m sure.

g.title: j877491754
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j844188697
g.text: But whatever was driving her wasn't like you.

g.title: j2080107959
g.text: This creature, this presence, is what we’re ultimately up against. I know that much now.

g.title: j1140594178
g.text: Giving it a name feels like I’ve gotten a tiny bit of control back.

g.title: j1186929354
g.text: Anything human about it was like a mockery.

g.title: j3238777200
g.text: Please tell me the truth. Do you believe there is any hope?

g.title: j2583408103
g.text: I’ve touched that thing with my mind. I thought I’d be probing Rusalka’s mind, but… the outer layers just caved in like wet, spongy plasterboard and then I was immersed in it. Floundering.

g.title: j278049215
g.text: It was about as human as a store mannequin. In pieces.

g.title: j2405859482
g.text: At this point? ... No.

g.title: j2483063964
g.text: Honestly? I'm... not sure.

g.title: j1422451222
g.text: Yes, I do.

g.title: j2186854149
g.text: Boolean EleanorIndifference is now true.

g.title: j3109756062
g.text: I touched it, you see. With my mind. I was trying to probe her, but she wasn't there.

g.title: j1356403214
g.text: At least you were honest.

g.title: j1163617270
g.text: I understand.

g.title: j3782653367
g.text: Don’t tell me why.

g.title: j2362032761
g.text: I know what you mean. We call it The Indifference.

g.title: j2442220509
g.text: Fine. Let hope die.

g.title: j3889254782
g.text: There's so much we don't know.

g.title: j2351369067
g.text: Just hold on to that belief. Let me feel it.

g.title: j2763646056
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j899177046
g.text: I'll keep fighting out of pure bloody stubbornness.

g.title: j527540089
g.text: After what's already happened this year, how are we supposed to make sane plans ever again?

g.title: j4221304659
g.text: Please.

g.title: j3634954244
g.text: Giving it a name feels like I’ve gotten a tiny bit of control back.

g.title: j732409284
g.text: Hate. Rage. Anything.

g.title: j3464309611
g.text: Maybe hope is a delusion. I don't know.

g.title: j3610076584
g.text: I reached out for Rusalka, and it was as if my fingers touched her face and went right through. The mask just collapsed.

g.title: j832186818
g.text: Boolean EleanorIndifference is now true.

g.title: j2033797117
g.text: Better than apathy. Better than meek surrender.

g.title: j3275934544
g.text: I could just really do with some right now.

g.title: j1494925676
g.text: What was underneath was like…

g.title: j1196611355
g.text: I’ve touched that thing with my mind. I thought I’d be probing Rusalka’s mind, but… the outer layers just caved in like wet, spongy plasterboard and then I was immersed in it. Floundering.

g.title: j454811037
g.text: I'm ready.

g.title: j3991134721
g.text: Ah, well. So it is. Even if we're stumbling onward through the dark, at least we have one another's company.

g.title: j2492618980
g.text: There’s a word. ‘Calenture.’ It’s a kind of madness that used to affect sailors. They’d become convinced that the green sea all around them wasn’t water at all, but green grass.

g.title: j694121446
g.text: They'd be compelled to jump from the ship down into the beautiful green meadows and go running across them. If a shipmate held them back, they’d fight.

g.title: j50629629
g.text: I jumped, expecting grass. Next second I was in over my head in the freezing dark.

g.title: j1742641432
g.text: Boolean EleanorIndifference2 is now true.

g.title: j3484555809
g.text: I don't think it's safe for you to talk about it like this.

g.title: j292363805
g.text: I’m here. Go on.

g.title: j3266517016
g.text: Well, shit.

g.title: j1399601314
g.text: There’s a feeling there isn’t a word for. You look out on the world and you just KNOW, that all the ordinariness - buildings, cars, people, jobs, work, routine - is just a thin crust over a bottomless horror, and if people ever realized it they’d start screaming and never stop.

g.title: j1128511912
g.text: I'd just about managed to psych myself up to this, and now, what? we're not mentioning the Devil in case it summons him?

g.title: j1198526827
g.text: I fell through the crust.

g.title: j3884754615
g.text: If you hear screaming in the night, it's me.

g.title: j3303082739
g.text: It wasn’t emptiness. I could have borne that. It went on and on forever, but it wasn’t just cold space. There was something in there with me.

g.title: j1166999307
g.text: An eye?

g.title: j410819468
g.text: A man trapped in a wall?

g.title: j3559210311
g.text: What was it?

g.title: j3862222236
g.text: I don’t know. But it knew I was there. It was AWARE of me. Like an elephant would be aware of a fly crawling across its eye.

g.title: j1520839732
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1496459983
g.text: I remember thinking ‘nothing that big should know I exist’.

g.title: j852934876
g.text: It felt such utter disregard for me, such monumental indifference that I wanted to stop existing on the spot.

g.title: j4097527957
g.text: It... does that.

g.title: j3878094245
g.text: What did you do?

g.title: j4028523467
g.text: I think I could have coped if it had hated me. Then I would have had some value, some significance. But it saw me as meaningless, and I saw what it saw. I was a speck. A nothing.

g.title: j3878214240
g.text: Everything I had ever been, every tender moment, every laugh, every morsel of Eleanor Nightingale blew away in that storm.

g.title: j3913259342
g.text: It felt my light fading, and I swear, a tiny tremor of satisfaction went through it. As if it was pleased to have crushed me. A flea under its fingernail.

g.title: j1681460616
g.text: But you came back, didn’t you? You’re still here. You proved that thing wrong.

g.title: j2512672163
g.text: Did I?

g.title: j3849913030
g.text: It’s still out there, isn’t it?

g.title: j3008294719
g.text: Yes, it is. But you’re still here, too.

g.title: j1264171395
g.text: The stars don’t stop burning just because space is big, cold and dark.

g.title: j316889407
g.text: Indifference wins in the end, my friend, no matter how many platitudes we throw into the abyss.

g.title: j2954331549
g.text: But they will stop burning. One day. The heat death of the Universe.

g.title: j3947777225
g.text: That’s the problem with not going mad. You’re cursed with clarity of thought.

g.title: j1490887012
g.text: You know what I’m talking about. You could have shattered like a sparrow’s egg or burnt your brain out with drugs until you felt nothing any more. And it would have hurt less than this… knowing.

g.title: j2084956401
g.text: I don’t understand why you haven’t walked away from this conversation yet.

g.title: j1033993608
g.text: Look. Entropy is real. I get that. Maybe the Great Indifference is the same thing. But whether it wins in the end, you don’t know and I don’t know either.

g.title: j996244687
g.text: I'm waiting for you to make up your mind, honestly. Do you want to take the easy way out and go insane? Or do you want to stand and fight?

g.title: j558502826
g.text: What I do know is that I’m not going to let it win NOW.

g.title: j4182609925
g.text: FIGHT HOW

g.title: j1263945758
g.text: So you’re putting up with my wails of existential despair as a battle tactic? That’s very Arthur of you.

g.title: j3029059824
g.text: IS THAT ALL YOU AND ARTHUR CAN UNDERSTAND? FIGHTING?

g.title: j1849232596
g.text: Actually, believe it or not, I care about you.

g.title: j2703993044
g.text: YOUR ANSWER TO THE UNDERLYING MEANINGLESSNESS OF EXISTENCE IS 'FIND A WAY TO PUNCH IT?'

g.title: j4233394724
g.text: I care about you too, mate. We’re squadmates. We've been through a lot.

g.title: j753243790
g.text: I can't believe I thought we had a single thing in common.

g.title: j690399614
g.text: It’s only fair to warn you that the good ship Eleanor may go down, either in the bloody sea or the night-black swamp, and you do not want to be on board when she does.

g.title: j2855929284
g.text: More fool me.

g.title: j1739418125
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j2864742878
g.text: Boolean EleanorNoDate is now true.

g.title: j3245098209
g.text: Thanks. You should go. I’ll be okay now. Honestly.
